1b:["$","section",null,{"className":"mt-10 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-slate-950","children":"Helpful article"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-5 grid gap-4 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-600","children":[["$","p","0",{"children":"The Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement is a practical tool for retirement planning that handles post-retirement budget calculations with precision. Budget Balance = Total Income − Total Expenses. Savings Rate = (Income − Expenses) ÷ Income × 100. 50/30/20 Rule: 50% needs, 30% wants, 20% savings and debt. Deficit = Expenses − Income (when negative)."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"Understanding how the calculation works helps you interpret results correctly. A budget is a forward-looking plan that matches expected income against planned spending. When expenses exceed income the result is a deficit; when income exceeds expenses the result is a surplus. The goal of budgeting is not to produce a number, but to identify where adjustments can be made before money runs out."}],["$","p","2",{"children":"Here is a concrete example of how the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement applies in a realistic retirement scenario: Monthly income: $5,200. Fixed expenses (rent, loan, insurance): $2,600. Variable expenses (food, transport, entertainment): $1,450. Savings contribution: $400. Budget balance: $5,200 − $2,600 − $1,450 − $400 = $750 surplus. Savings rate: ($400 + $750) ÷ $5,200 = 22.1% — above the 20% target."}],["$","p","3",{"children":"Tips for accurate results: Track actual spending against the budget at least monthly and adjust the next month's plan based on what happened. A budget that is never reviewed quickly becomes irrelevant to real financial behavior."}],["$","p","4",{"children":"When to use this calculator: Use the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement when starting a new retirement spending plan, reviewing whether current habits match stated goals, or preparing for a major financial change like a job switch, new expense, or income drop."}],["$","p","5",{"children":"A common mistake to avoid: Forgetting irregular expenses — annual subscriptions, car maintenance, holiday gifts, medical copays — is the most reliable way to blow a budget. Divide annual irregular costs by 12 and include them as a monthly line item."}],["$","p","6",{"children":"The Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement is one of many retirement tools designed to turn complex formulas into clear, actionable numbers. Use realistic inputs, change one variable at a time, and compare results to build genuine confidence in your post-retirement budget decisions."}]]}]]}]
1c:["$","section",null,{"className":"mt-10 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-slate-950","children":"Frequently asked questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-5 space-y-4","children":[["$","details","What is the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement best used for?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"What is the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement best used for?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"It is designed for post retirement budget problems in retirement planning. Use it when you need a quick, accurate answer to a post-retirement budget question without building a spreadsheet or doing manual arithmetic. It is especially useful when you want to compare two scenarios by changing one input at a time."}]]}],["$","details","How accurate are the results from the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"How accurate are the results from the Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"The calculator applies the standard formula for post-retirement budget and produces results accurate to four decimal places. The accuracy of the output depends entirely on the accuracy of the inputs — garbage in, garbage out. Use realistic numbers based on your actual situation for the most useful results."}]]}],["$","details","Can I use this Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement for professional retirement planning?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"Can I use this Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement for professional retirement planning?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"Yes, as a planning and estimation tool. The formulas are standard and widely used in retirement contexts. For legally binding decisions, tax filings, or clinical assessments, verify critical results with a qualified professional. This calculator gives you the right numbers to start the conversation."}]]}],["$","details","What happens if I enter zero or leave a field blank?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"What happens if I enter zero or leave a field blank?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"The calculator will either return zero, produce an error message, or show an undefined result — depending on which field is blank and what the formula requires. Fill in all required fields with realistic values for a valid result. Some calculators accept zero for optional inputs (like an initial balance of $0)."}]]}],["$","details","Is this Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement free to use?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"Is this Post-Retirement Budget Calculator | Retirement free to use?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"Yes — completely free, with no account required, no ads, and no hidden costs. The tool is designed for fast, accessible retirement planning across all devices. All calculations happen instantly in your browser and no data is stored or transmitted."}]]}]]}]]}]
